Fascinating, crazy, maybe a little scary. 迷人疯狂也许有点可怕

I mean it sounds like we're talking about 听起来我们讨论的不仅仅
not just using something to help humans do their jobs,
是使用某种东西来帮助人类完成他们的工作
but just replacing it entirely. 而是完全取代它

Could this be a new normal, on a large scale? 这会是一种大规模的新常态吗

===
I this is the thing, right, as a tech correspondent 多年来作为一名科技记者
for years, i've had companies tell me, you know, "well this technology"
我一直有公司告诉我
"is for augmenting a human or making a human job a little bit easier."
这项技术是为了增强人类或让人类的工作变得更容易

In this case, it is truly right out and out there to replace a human worker, Amazon warehouse workers.
在这种情况下它确实可以取代人类工人，亚马逊仓库工人
【ɪn ðɪs keɪ sɪ dɪs trµ li raɪ daʊ’ ðeər də rɪ pleɪ sə hjµ mən wər kər.】

That's one of the largest employers in America. 那是美国最大的雇主之一
People really go for that job. 人们再大量地做那份工作

And so we're really I think at this sort of historic（历史性地） turning point where suddenly
因此 我认为我们真的处于这样一个历史性的转折点
it's no longer the case of when could technology
突然之间技术何时能取代一系列工作不再是问题
replace a set of jobs, but this is truly something that's built to do that.
但这确实是为了做到这一点而建造的东西